04:26.787 --> 04:29.232
Hands off, you big blue Buttinski!

04:30.835 --> 04:32.852
Blood, bile, spinal fluid,

04:32.858 --> 04:34.442
blood, other, phlegm,

04:34.446 --> 04:36.013
miscellaneous ooze...

04:37.955 --> 04:40.761
Grampa's driving me crazy.

04:40.768 --> 04:43.023
Why are you telling me?He's your father-in-law.

04:43.026 --> 04:45.381
Can we at least get out of the house for an evening?

04:45.387 --> 04:48.691
Sure, but I think you're exaggerating the problem.

04:48.698 --> 04:49.853
I'm scared.

04:49.857 --> 04:51.603
Can I sleep across you?

04:54.846 --> 04:56.812
No!

04:59.868 --> 05:01.892
What are you doing here, Patty or Selma?

05:01.895 --> 05:04.132
I invited Selma here

05:04.137 --> 05:06.322
to watch Grandpa watch the kids.

05:06.328 --> 05:08.183
For some reason,she doesn't trust him.

05:08.188 --> 05:10.981
Maybe it's the bang-up job he did raising you.

05:10.985 --> 05:12.820
He was a great dad.

05:12.828 --> 05:14.770
Every year he got so mad

05:14.777 --> 05:16.913
when Santa didn't bring me presents.

05:19.716 --> 05:20.750
Um...

05:21.647 --> 05:23.123
lemon candy?

05:23.126 --> 05:24.012
No thanks.

05:24.028 --> 05:25.230
I brought my own.

05:43.905 --> 05:45.263
I know what you're wondering.

05:45.268 --> 05:47.760
How come a single woman with so much to offer

05:47.768 --> 05:49.703
is alone on a Saturday night.

05:49.707 --> 05:53.132
I assumed you were resting up for bingo tomorrow, like me.

05:53.938 --> 05:57.323
My numbers don't get called much these days.

05:57.338 --> 05:58.591
